(605, '2026-04-09', 'Day Shift', 17, 'Redsky Morning Shift Report\n\nF0.5 WIFI = Device 615621 experienced an outage at 08:23, receiving low signal and interference. The solution was to replace the TP-UP and wake-up cable.\n\nF1. RF OTA = Device 615539, using ZigBee TX power, sometimes turned off and staking itself due to unstable Tektronix. The solution was to replace Tektronix and try retesting with a pass/OK.\nDevice 615542, using ZigBee frequency, sometimes turned off and staking itself due to unstable Tektronix. The solution was to replace Tektronix and try restarting the PC and retrying the online test with a pass/OK.\nDevice 615624, sometimes turned off and staking itself due to unstable Tektronix. The solution was to replace Tektronix and try reverifying the values ​​and testing with a pass/OK.\n\nF2. RF TXRX = DEVICE 61550 ng zwave packet some of the items that have been retested are still ng.\ndevice 615551 ng zwave packet re-verify.\ndevice 615529 ng zigbe packet try to find the value with golden to verify', 62, '2026-04-09 08:53:00'),
