(647, '2026-04-13', 'Day Shift', 17, 'Redsky morning shift report\n\nF0. Board = Device 615515 NG LTE Module from 8:28 AM to exactly 9:18 AM. This was due to the fixture needle being unusable or NG, and NG timing out of some of the components and the fixture machine.\n\nF0.5 WiFi = Device 615531 NG CAPTURE SIGNAL and NG had low values, and the NG device was TIRED. The solution was to replace the T-Plug and banana cable of the fixture.\n\nF1 RF OTA = Device 615628 NG WiFi TX power due to incorrect values ​​from Tektronix to the machine, requiring re-verification. OK/pass\n\nF2. RFTXRX = Device 615549 NG ZigBee packet. The solution was to verify golden. Device 615629 NG ZigBe packet. The solution was to re-verify golden. Device 615631 NG ZWave packet. because the golden position changes so that the resulting value is less stable, recalibration is needed', 62, '2026-04-13 08:02:17'),
